description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7926/documentation

[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



This dataset describes the energy consumption and the emissions linked to the transport of 1 tkm Russian natural gas in an onshore pipeline.
category: H:Transportation and storage/49:Land transport and transport via pipelines/493:Transport via pipeline/4930:Transport via pipeline

processDocumentation.timeDescription: The data for emissions is from 1994, the data for energy requirements from 2001.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The data for emissions and for energy requirements is based on German data.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Long-distance gas transport onshore with average compressor station.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: none This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography RU. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.

(2007) reintroduced for v3.9 to reflect that the reference product of 'natural gas, burned in gas turbine' was changed back to the fuel input (rather than the output of electricity).
